also since SQL server 2005 you can create an index with included columns&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
INCLUDE ( column [ ,... n ] )&lt;br /&gt;
Specifies the non-key columns to be added to the leaf level of the nonclustered index. The nonclustered index can be unique or non-unique.&lt;br /&gt;
